      "content": "Subject: Your Application for Senior DevOps Engineer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to personally thank you for your interest in the Senior DevOps Engineer position at our Austin-based company. We were truly impressed by your skills, experience, and the enthusiasm you brought to the final round of interviews.\n\nInterviewing for these roles is no small feat, and we deeply appreciate the time and effort you invested in the application process. We understand that it can be disheartening to not move forward, but please know that your talents and abilities would have been a great asset to our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with a candidate who has a bit more experience with Kubernetes orchestration. This decision was not easy, and we value the opportunity to have had you on our team. We encourage you to keep an eye on our careers page for future roles specifically in the DevOps space, as we believe your skills and experience would be a great fit.\n\nWe wish you the best of luck in your job search and future endeavors. Thank you once again for your interest in our company.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
